Button labels:
Initialize buttons
O: Online
Rollback is also performed on updates of virtuals within a transaction.
Therefore WTD is to be set to '' before entering the transaction to prevent
to prevent returning online.(test with update WTD = '' in TP resulted in loop)
M:Modify selected schedule
N:New Schedule
If a schedule number is returned, continue with new schedule, else go to online
F: ConFirm
A; Approve
E: RElease
-- Msg: Booking of invoices already started
-- Msg: Schedule is being processed, please try again later
S: OK/Save/Select
Close current transaction
Process selected schedule through OSP001B
Return to main screen
Return Online with new range
N: New
Close current transaction
Create new schedule through OSP002
Return to main screen
D: Delete
Delete selected schedule
Exit current task and return Online
E: rElease remove active user and set to unfinished, own transaction for locks
F: Confirm, Close transaction and call BSP012 to confirm and book (if allowed)
A: Approve Close task and call BSP012 to approve and book
Confirmation is pointless (rollback too), all changes are final anyway
Only allow subtask to be accessed as long as no other action initiated
